      },
      "date": "2015-11-05 22:17:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nIt isn't perfect, but definitely looks like it will solve the problem of too many threads being started.\n\nThe other question is whether the maximum number of blocking threads is too high?  Should that be limited by the number of cores on the client or similar so it doesn't get out of control?  Having too many threads also causes lock contention for little benefit.",
